  "body": "```go\r\nmaxRequestContentLength = 1024 * 1024 * 5\r\n```\r\n```go\r\ntype jsonrpcMessage struct {\r\n\tVersion string          `json:\"jsonrpc,omitempty\"`\r\n\tID      json.RawMessage `json:\"id,omitempty\"`\r\n\tMethod  string          `json:\"method,omitempty\"`\r\n\tParams  json.RawMessage `json:\"params,omitempty\"`\r\n\tError   *jsonError      `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\r\n\tResult  json.RawMessage `json:\"result,omitempty\"`\r\n}\r\n```\r\nI guess, most of the content exists in jsonrpcMessage.Params in normal.\r\nBut, i concern the case that filled dummy data to jsonrpcMessage.Version or jsonrpcMessage.Method.\r\n\r\nThe request normal,\r\n```\r\n{\"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBlockNumber\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd bad requests,\r\n```\r\nmethodDummy := \"aaaaaaaaa ... aaaa\" // len(methodDummy): 5242000\r\n{\"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\"method\":methodDummy,\"params\":[],\"id\":1}\r\n```\r\n```\r\njsonrpcDummy := \"aaaaaaaaa ... aaaa\" // len(jsonrpcDummy): 5242000\r\n{\"jsonrpc\" : jsonrpcDummy,\"method\":\"eth_getBlockNumber\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}\r\n```\r\nThese requests will fail, but return error after unmarshalling.\r\nIt doesn't matter if it's necessary work, but wouldn't it be better to reduce it if not necessary.\r\n\r\ni'll open a PR that relate to the idea.\r\nRefer that PR.\r\n\r\nThanks.\r\n",
